{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04257/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04257"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:42:57"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low, over the shoulder"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld, pan, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman glances at a door with a peephole."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04257/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04257","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04257/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04257"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04257/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04257/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04257/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04257/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04257/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04257/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04257/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04257/canvas/1/100c1ad7-a090-4aa5-870e-3d0068ad9452","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:35:49.930Z","creator":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04257/manifest.json","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Although <em>Phantom Thread</em>’s primary Hitchcock reference is <em>Rebecca</em> (1940), <em>Rear Window</em> (1954) also looms large. The connection is made explicit here as Reynolds and Alma peer at one another through the peephole during the fashion show. Much as in <em>Rear Window</em>—Grace Kelly’s Lisa Fremont finally gets James Stewart’s L.B. Jefferies to see her adventurous side when she helps him solve the mystery of the missing woman in the building across the alley from his apartment—Alma romances Reynolds by taking charge (even poisoning him), practicing his trade (sewing), and becoming part of the House of Woodcock. Both films, too, play with their protagonists’ wounded sense of masculinity. PTA spoke about the <em>Rebecca</em> and <em>Rear Window</em> influences in an interview with Story Classique (Xixax TV, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW242881624 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6BQg4mYGVjY\"><u>PHANTOM THREAD - Paul Thomas Anderson French interview</u></a>”), at the Palm Springs International Film Festival (Shackleton, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW242881624 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=au7NMfNWrhE\"><u>PHANTOM THREAD Q&amp;A</u></a>”), and in his conversation with director Rian Johnson (Xixax TV, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW242881624 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=faVGtuna5PE\"><u>PHANTOM THREAD - AUDIO - Paul Thomas Anderson interviewed by Rian Johnson</u></a>”). See Ethan Warren’s <em>The Cinema of Paul Thomas Anderson</em> (p. 54–55) for a consideration of the Hitchcock influence.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04257/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:319.1386271870794,300.3230148048453,374.6971736204576,324.30686406460296"}}}]}]}]}